  "text": "Stack protection mechanisms in the LLVM project (repo: sg-evals/llvm-project--a8f3c97d) are implemented across several files:\n\n1. **StackProtector pass** (`llvm/lib/CodeGen/StackProtector.cpp`): This is the primary LLVM pass that inserts stack protector checks. It defines the `StackProtector` class (a `FunctionPass`) and the static function `InsertStackProtectors`. The pass adds a stack canary (guard value) in the function prologue and checks it in the epilogue, calling `__stack_chk_fail` if the canary has been corrupted. It also contains `SSPLayoutAnalysis::requiresStackProtector` which determines whether a function needs protection.\n\n2. **SafeStack pass** (`llvm/lib/CodeGen/SafeStack.cpp`): Implements the SafeStack instrumentation that separates safe and unsafe stack allocations. Defines the `SafeStack` class (the core transformation) and `SafeStackLegacyPass` (the legacy pass wrapper). It moves unsafe allocations (those that could be exploited via buffer overflows) to a separate unsafe stack, while keeping safe allocations on the regular stack. Also includes `llvm/lib/CodeGen/SafeStackLayout.cpp` for the frame layout logic.\n\n3. **Header file** (`llvm/include/llvm/CodeGen/StackProtector.h`): Declares the `StackProtector` (legacy FunctionPass) and `StackProtectorPass` (new pass manager) classes that form the stack protection pass interface. Also `llvm/include/llvm/CodeGen/SafeStack.h` declares `SafeStackPass`.\n\n4. **Runtime `__stack_chk_fail` implementation** (`libc/src/compiler/generic/__stack_chk_fail.cpp`): Provides the `__stack_chk_fail()` function that is called at runtime when a stack buffer overflow is detected (canary mismatch). It writes 'stack smashing detected' to stderr and aborts. Note: this is in `libc/src/compiler/` rather than `compiler-rt/lib/builtins/` in this repository version.\n\n5. **Memory safety instrumentation** (`llvm/lib/Transforms/Instrumentation/AddressSanitizer.cpp`): Implements the AddressSanitizer pass which includes the `FunctionStackPoisoner` struct that instruments stack frame allocations with poisoned redzones to detect stack buffer overflows, use-after-return, and use-after-scope bugs. This is the primary memory safety instrumentation file related to stack frame protection in `llvm/lib/Transforms/Instrumentation/`."
